history.content: Even if you get B-, you will still be able to declare cs. So if you are worried about that, I would suggest you speak to one of the GSI's. I am sure their advice will help you a lot. Ans also remember that you should work hard (at least as much as for 61A) so as to get A- on 61B.

children.subject: Do practice exams and go to office hours to ask TA questions. Homework difficulty is more geared toward the difficult part of the exam, and it also helps you understand the concepts. I would suggest everyone to do or at least understand the HW to study for exam.

Does anyone have any tips on how to study for CS 70? There's not a lot of tests from Professor Rao and the other professors' tests seem very different from his. Are there any textbooks, outside sources, or tests from another professor that I can use as practice problems?

I took the homework option in hopes that I would not have to study as much for the tests but it still seems like the homework doesn't do much towards test preparation.

history.content:
I performed almost 1 STD below the avg on the 70 midterm. I am doing hw + test option and my hw grade so far has been perfect.

I got an A- in 61a and am confident in getting at least an A- in 61b which I am taking right now.

However, I have heard that the class only becomes more difficult from this point on and am worried about declaring as LS CS. Should I drop 70?
